NAN Senate President Abubakar Bukola Saraki has appointed 59-year old Earl Osaro Onaiwu as Liaison Officer on State Matters. This was disclosed in a statement issued by Yusuph Olaniyonu, Special Adviser (Media and Publicity) to Senate President. READ ALSO: Family alleges IPOB member goes into hiding over alleged threat to life Onaiwu, an experienced politician and public administrator will help to co-ordinate relationship between the Office of the Senate President and the various state governments across the country. Earl Osaro Osaze Onaiwu is a former Director-General of the PDP Governors Forum and the gubernatorial nominee for the All Progressives Grand Alliance in the 2016 election in Edo state.